{
  "text": "In drosophila Shaker (Kv1), Shab (Kv2) and squid sqKv2 channels, the position corresponding to I400 in Kv1.1 is also an I-to-V editing site, which represents a clear case of convergent evolution [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In addition to the previously reported functional consequences for editing at this paralogous position [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] , we found that Shaker and Shab channels have also a reduced HUFA sensitivity when they undergo this conserved I-to-V editing.",
  "correct_citation": {
